🔹 Approval kya hai?
SailPoint me Approval sirf Identity changes ke liye nahi hota, ye kisi bhi object change ke liye ho sakta hai,
Approval SailPoint me kisi bhi identity/sailpoint_object change ko confirm karne ka process hai.
Jaise identity me change hota hai (role assign, entitlement add, identity disable, etc.) → Approval workflow trigger hota hai
Approval workflow decide karta hai: ye change accept hoga ya reject
🔹 Approval ke Components:-
Request → Identity change ke liye request
Approver → Jo person / role approve karega
Workflow → Process jo approval check kare
Status → PENDING / APPROVED / REJECTED.


Approval ka matlab:-
Approval = Kisi request ko authorize karna ya allow karna.
Jab koi user request (jaise new account create, role assign) submit karta hai,
to system ya organization ek approver decide karta hai ki ye request sahi hai ya nahi.
Approver approve kare → request aage process hoti hai
Approver reject kare → request cancel ho jati hai
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Approval kya hai?
👉 Approval = kisi request ko allow ya deny karne ka process
Simple line:-
👉 “Kya ye change karna allowed hai ya nahi — iska decision”

🔥 SailPoint me Approval ka matlab:-
👉 Jab koi user kuch change request karta hai, jaise:
Role lena
Access lena
Email update
Account enable/disable
👉 To system direct change nahi karta ❌
👉 Pehle Approval process chalta hai ✅

🔹 Approval me kya hota hai?
1️⃣ Request create hota hai:-
User → request bhejta hai

2️⃣ ApprovalRequest banta hai:-
Poora request container

3️⃣ ApprovalItems bante hain:-
Har kaam ke liye alag item

4️⃣ Approver decide karta hai:-
👉 Approver ho sakta hai:-
Manager
Admin
Security team

5️⃣ Decision hota hai:-
APPROVE ✅
REJECT ❌

6️⃣ Final result:-
👉 Agar approve:-
System change apply karega

👉 Agar reject:-
Koi change nahi hoga.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointFactory;
import sailpoint.object.Approval;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.object.ApprovalRequest;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class ApprovalExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        // 1️⃣ SailPoint Context
        SailPointContext context = SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext();

        // 2️⃣ Identity fetch
        Identity user = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "kishan");

        // 3️⃣ Approval Request create
        ApprovalRequest request = new ApprovalRequest();
        request.setName("Role Assignment");
        request.setTargetIdentity(user);
        request.setAction("ASSIGN_ROLE");

        // 4️⃣ Approvers set
        List<String> approvers = new ArrayList<>();
        approvers.add("rohith");  // manager
        request.setApprovers(approvers);

        // 5️⃣ Approval create and trigger
        Approval approval = context.createObject(Approval.class);
        approval.setRequest(request);
        approval.setStatus("PENDING");
        context.saveObject(approval);

        System.out.println("Approval created for identity: " + user.getName());
        System.out.println("Status: " + approval.getStatus());

        // 6️⃣ Simulate Approver action
        approval.approve();
        context.saveObject(approval);

        System.out.println("After approval, Status: " + approval.getStatus());
    }
}
🔹 Expected Output:-
Approval created for identity: kishan
Status: PENDING
After approval, Status: APPROVED
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Approval Class Methods List (without description):-
getStatus()
setStatus(String status)
getRequest()
setRequest(ApprovalRequest request)
getApprovers()
setApprovers(List<String> approvers)
getComments()
setComments(List<String> comments)
approve()
reject()
isApproved()
isRejected()
getCreated()
setCreated(Date date)
getModified()
setModified(Date date)
getCreatedBy()
setCreatedBy(String user)
getModifiedBy()
setModifiedBy(String user)
getId()
setId(String id)
clone()
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
toString()
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ Status related methods:-
Method	                              Kya karta hai
getStatus():----------------Current status return karta hai (PENDING / APPROVED / REJECTED)
setStatus(String status):---Status set karta hai manually
isApproved():---------------Returns true agar status APPROVED hai.
isRejected():---------------Returns true agar status REJECTED hai.

Example:-
Approval approval = new Approval();
approval.setStatus("PENDING");
System.out.println("Status: " + approval.getStatus()); // PENDING

approval.approve(); 
System.out.println("Approved? " + approval.isApproved()); // true
System.out.println("Status now: " + approval.getStatus()); // APPROVED

Output:-
Status: PENDING
Approved? true
Status now: APPROVED
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ Request related methods:-
Method	                                                   Kya karta hai
getRequest()	                          Jo ApprovalRequest associated hai return karta hai
setRequest(ApprovalRequest request)	      Approval me request assign karta hai
ApprovalRequest req = new ApprovalRequest("Request-123");
approval.setRequest(req);
System.out.println("Request ID: " + approval.getRequest().getId());
Output:-
Request ID: Request-123
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 3️⃣ Approvers / Comments methods:-
Method	                                              Kya karta hai
getApprovers():------------------------------Approvers ki list return karta hai.
setApprovers(List<String> approvers):--------List set karta hai
getComments():-------------------------------Comments list return karta hai
setComments(List<String> comments):----------Comments set karta hai

List<String> approvers = new ArrayList<String>();
approvers.add("Alice");
approvers.add("Bob");
approval.setApprovers(approvers);
System.out.println("Approvers: " + approval.getApprovers());

List<String> comments = new ArrayList<String>();
comments.add("Looks good");
approval.setComments(comments);
System.out.println("Comments: " + approval.getComments());

Output:-
Approvers: [Alice, Bob]
Comments: [Looks good]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 4️⃣ Action methods:-
Method	                             Kya karta hai
approve()	Status APPROVED set karta hai, isApproved() true ho jata hai
reject()	Status REJECTED set karta hai, isRejected() true ho jata hai
approval.reject();
System.out.println("Rejected? " + approval.isRejected()); // true
System.out.println("Status now: " + approval.getStatus()); // REJECTED

Output:-
Rejected? true
Status now: REJECTED
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5️⃣ Created / Modified / User methods:-
Method	                                         Kya karta hai
getCreated() / setCreated(Date date)	       Approval creation date set / get
getModified() / setModified(Date date)	       Last modified date set / get
getCreatedBy() / setCreatedBy(String user)	   Created by user set / get
getModifiedBy() / setModifiedBy(String user)   Modified by user set / get
approval.setCreated(new Date());
approval.setCreatedBy("Admin");
System.out.println("Created by: " + approval.getCreatedBy());
Output:-
Created by: Admin
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 6️⃣ Object / Utility methods:-
Method	                                     Kya karta hai
getId() / setId(String id)	     Approval object ka unique ID set / get
clone()	                         Approval object copy banata hai
equals(Object obj)	             Compare karta hai do Approval objects
hashCode()	                     Object hash return karta hai
toString()	                     Approval object ka readable string return karta hai
approval.setId("APP-001");
System.out.println(approval.toString());

Output (example):-
Approval{id='APP-001', status='REJECTED', approvers=[Alice, Bob], comments=[Looks good]}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
